# gstack + ContentOps AI

This repo uses [GStack + GBrain](https://github.com/garrytan/gstack) for **engineering quality and memory**, and ContentOps' 11 agents for **marketing operations**.

**Installed:** gstack at `~/.cursor/skills/gstack` (55 skills) · gbrain PGLite at `~/.gbrain/` · repo indexed as `contenthack` · see `AGENTS.md`

## When to use gstack (Cursor agent)

Load gstack skills for code, infra, and product work — not for generating campaign copy.

| Task | gstack skill | Why |
|------|-------------|-----|
| New feature / rethink scope | `/office-hours` then `/autoplan` | CEO + eng + design review before code |
| Architecture / API design | `/plan-eng-review` | Locks data flow, edge cases, tests |
| Code review before merge | `/review` | Production bug patterns, auto-fix trivial issues |
| Security audit | `/cso` | OWASP + STRIDE on auth, MCP, API routes |
| Test staging / dashboard | `/qa` + `/browse` | Real browser verification — use `/browse`, not generic browser MCP |
| Ship PR | `/ship` | Tests, coverage, PR creation |
| Deploy verify | `/land-and-deploy` then `/canary` | Post-deploy health checks |
| Debug production issue | `/investigate` | Root-cause before fixes |
| Second opinion (cross-model) | `/codex` | Independent review from another model |
| Cross-agent browser pairing | `/pair-agent` | Bridge Cursor with remote agents |

## When to use ContentOps agents (app logic)

Use `lib/agents/` orchestrator and `lib/models/routing.ts` for campaign workflow:

`research → strategy → content → video → safety → scheduler → publisher → leadfinder → outreach → analytics`

Model routing (GPT-4o, o4-mini, Kimi K2.5) lives in `lib/models/routing.ts` — do not duplicate in prompts.

## Two-layer architecture

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  gstack (engineering layer)                              │
│  plan → build → review → qa → ship → deploy → canary    │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
                          builds/maintains
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  ContentOps (product layer)                              │
│  11 specialized agents + model routing + MCP bridge      │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

## Competitive advantage

- **gstack**: repeatable engineering process (23 specialist skills) — fewer production bugs, faster ship cycles, cross-model review via `/codex`.
- **ContentOps**: domain-specific agent orchestration with cost-aware model routing — cheap models for drafts, quality models for research/safety/outreach.
- **Together**: ship marketing AI product faster *and* with production-grade code quality.

## Defaults

- Web browsing for QA/staging: gstack `/browse` (`~/.cursor/skills/gstack/browse/dist/browse`)
- MCP bridge: `.trae/mcp.json` → `scripts/trae-contentops-mcp.mjs`
- Demo mode: `NEXT_PUBLIC_DEMO_MODE=true` — use for local QA without API keys
